canonical:
  title: 銀燭朝天
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 銀燭誰當秉勤王一代賢九街猶踏月雙闕早朝天馬首飛紅焰螭頭散碧煙春風吹漏盡曉影隔花燃衣暖香薰麝冠寒露濕蟬鴛行纔整後召赴大平筵
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 銀燭朝天
  author: 無名氏
  language: lzh
  text: 銀燭誰當秉。勤王一代賢。九街猶踏月。雙闕早朝天。馬首飛紅焰。螭頭散碧煙。春風吹漏盡。曉影隔花燃。衣暖香薰麝。冠寒露濕蟬。鴛行纔整後。召赴大平筵。
korean:
  title: 은촉 조천
  author: 무명씨
  language: kor
  text: |-
    은촉을 누가 마땅히 잡아야 할까
    왕사에 부지런한 일대의 현신
    구가엔 아직도 달을 밟는데
    쌍궐에 일찍 임금께 조회
    말 머리에 새빨간 불꽃이 튀고
    이두에 파란 연기가 흩어지네
    봄 바람이 누수를 불어 다하는데
    새벽 〈촛불〉 그림자 옆에서 타고 있네
    따스한 옷에 사향이 물씬 배들고
    찬 이슬에 선관이 축축이 젖네
    이윽고 조신들이 열지어 선 뒤
    불리어 태평연으로 향하여 가네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0140_010_0430&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Silver Candle at Court
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Who shall bear the silver candle?
    Faithful ministers of a worthy age,
    still treading moonlight through the nine streets,
    early approaching the twin gates for audience with the throne.
    Sparks of crimson flame dance from the horses' heads,
    tendrils of blue smoke drift from the dragon finials.
    Spring wind blows the water clock to emptiness,
    while candlelight flickers in the dawn beside the flowers.
    Warm robes perfumed with musk,
    cold dew dampens the official's crown.
    At last the courtiers stand in ordered ranks,
    summoned forth to the great banquet of peace.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'nine streets' refers to the capital city's layout; 'twin gates' refers to the palace gates where officials gathered for court audience.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'water clock' (漏) marks time through the night; its emptying signals the transition from night to dawn.
  - key: ''
    value: This poem celebrates the loyalty and ceremony of court officials attending dawn audience, with particular attention to the visual splendor of official procession.
